A 26-year-old plumber, Paul Aduma, yesterday appeared at a Tinubu Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly stealing 75 pieces of PVC plumbing pipes valued at N150,000. The pipes are said to belong to his employer Mr Sunday Nwazor. Aduma pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Fidelis Dike alleged that the defendant committed the offence on January 16, around 4:15am, at Road I, Bakery bus stop, Badore, Ajah, Lagos. He said the defendant conspired with two other labourers (at large) to steal the pipes at a building site. Magistrate T. A. Anjorin-Ajose granted the defendant N50,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. Anjorin-Ajose said the sureties must be responsible and credible. The case continues on March 18.